{"title_page": "Kotwan", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=July 2018}}\n{{original research|date=August 2018}}\n{{more footnotes|date=August 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{EngvarB|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Kotwan\n| other_name              =\n| nickname                =\n| settlement_type         = Village\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           =\n| pushpin_map             = India Uttar Pradesh#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         =\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|27.82|N|77.42|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{IND}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Mathura district|Mathura]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        =\n| founder                 =\n| named_for               =\n| government_type         =\n| governing_body          =\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          =\n| area_rank               =\n| area_total_km2          =\n| elevation_footnotes     =\n| elevation_m             = 189\n| population_total        = 5193\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         =\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n| population_footnotes    = <ref>[http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=140007 Census of India]</ref>\n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Hindi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 281403\n| registration_plate      = UP-85\n| area_code_type          = Telephone code\n| area_code               = 05662\n| website                 =\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n\n'''Kotwan'''  is a village in the [[Mathura district]] of [[Uttar Pradesh]], India. It is the site where according to [[Hinduism]], [[Krishna]] spent his childhood and is one of the main places in the [[Braj|Braj Bhoomi]] region.<ref>{{cite web|title=UP gets officially designated \u2018teerth sthals\u2019 in Kotwan related to Sheetal Kund}}</ref> The Village is about 100&nbsp;km away from [[Agra, Uttar Pradesh|Agra]].\n\n== Geography ==\nKotwan is located at {{Coord|27.82578745|N|77.42016748312331|E|}}, in the Mathura District of Uttar Pradesh, India. It belongs to Agra Division. It is located 55&nbsp;km towards North from District headquarters Mathura, 10&nbsp;km from Nandgaon, and 429&nbsp;km from state capital Lucknow.\n\nNabipur (3&nbsp;km), Hatana (4&nbsp;km), Lalpur (5&nbsp;km ), Kharauth (5&nbsp;km), Bathain Khurd (6&nbsp;km) are the nearby villages to Kotwan. Kotwan is surrounded by Chhata Block towards East, Hodal Block towards North, Hassanpur Block towards North, and Punahana Block towards west.\n\nHodal, Palwal, Vrindavan, Mathura are the cities nearby Kotwan.\n\nKotwan is located at the border of the Mathura District and Bharatpur District. Bharatpur District Kaman is located to the west of it. It is near to the Haryana-UP Border.\n\n== Demographics ==\n\n===Kotwan 2011 Census Details===\n\nKotwan Local Language is Hindi. Kotwan Village Total population is 5193 and number of houses are 802. Female Population is 47.2%. Village literacy rate is 58.0% and the Female Literacy rate is 21.8%.\n\n===Population===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Census Parameter!! Census Data\n|-\n| Total Population || 5193 \n|-\n| Total no. Of Houses || 802\n|-\n| Female Population % || 47.2% (2452)\n|-\n| Total Literacy Rate % || 58% (3013)\n|-\n| Female Literacy rate %, || 21.8% (1134)\n|-\n| Schedule Tribes Population % || 0.0% (00)\n|-\n| Schedule Cast Population % || 19.6% (1019)\n|-\n| Working Population % ||24.5%\n|-\n| Child (0-6) Population || 790\n|-\n| Girl Child (0-6) Population %|| 44.4% (351)\n|}\n\n== Religious heritage ==\n\nKotwan is considered to be a holy place for [[Vaisnavism]] tradition of [[Hinduism]]. It is a related to worship of Braj and the area includes places like [[Sheetal Kund|Kotwan]] that are associated with Krishna. Millions of devotees of [[Radha Krishna]] visit these places of pilgrimage every year and participate in a number of festivals. The center of Krishna-worship has been for a long time Brajbhumi, the district of Mathura that embraces also Vrindavana, Govardhana, and Gokula, associated with Krishna from the time immemorial. Many millions of Krishna ''bhaktas'' visit these places every year and participate in the numerous festivals that re-enact divine scenes from Krishna's life on Earth, of which were spent in those very places.\n\n==Transportation==\n\n===Road===\nKotwan is well connected by roads and is connected to [[Delhi]] by [[National Highway 2 (India)|National Highway (NH) 2]]<ref name=route>{{cite web |title=NHAI |url=http://www.nhai.org/NH2_Delhi_Kolkata_main.htm |accessdate=February 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161204065036/http://www.nhai.org/NH2_Delhi_Kolkata_main.htm |archive-date=4 December 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Rail===\n*'''Kosi Kalan Rail Station''' is on the Old G.T. Road Kosi Kalan.\n*'''Hodal Rail Station''' is on the Agra-Delhi Road.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Mathura district]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=July 2018}}\n{{original research|date=August 2018}}\n{{more footnotes|date=August 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{EngvarB|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Kotwan\n| other_name              =\n| nickname                =\n| settlement_type         = Village\n| image_alt               =\n| image_caption           =\n| pushpin_map             = India Uttar Pradesh#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         =\n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|27.82|N|77.42|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{IND}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Mathura district|Mathura]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        =\n| founder                 =\n| named_for               =\n| government_type         =\n| governing_body          =\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          =\n| area_rank               =\n| area_total_km2          =\n| elevation_footnotes     =\n| elevation_m             = 189\n| population_total        = 5193\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         =\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      =\n| population_footnotes    = <ref>[http://www.censusindia.gov.in/pca/SearchDetails.aspx?Id=140007 Census of India]</ref>\n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Hindi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 281403\n| registration_plate      = UP-85\n| area_code_type          = Telephone code\n| area_code               = 05662\n| website                 =\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n\n'''Kotwan'''  is a village in the [[Mathura district]] of [[Uttar Pradesh]], India. It is the site where according to [[Hinduism]], [[Krishna]] spent his childhood and is one of the main places in the [[Braj|Braj Bhoomi]] region.<ref>{{cite web|title=UP gets officially designated \u2018teerth sthals\u2019 in Kotwan related to Sheetal Kund}}</ref> The Village is about 100&nbsp;km away from [[Agra, Uttar Pradesh|Agra]].\n\n== Geography ==\nKotwan is located at {{Coord|27.82578745|N|77.42016748312331|E|}}, in the Mathura District of Uttar Pradesh State, India. It belongs to Agra Division. It is located 55 KM towards North from District head quarters Mathura, 10 KM from Nandgaon, and 429 KM from state capital Lucknow.\n\nNabipur (3KM), Hatana (4KM), Lalpur (5KM ), Kharauth (5KM), Bathain Khurd (6 KM) are the nearby villages to Kotwan. Kotwan is surrounded by Chhata Block towards East, Hodal Block towards North, Hassanpur Block towards North, and Punahana Block towards west.\n\nHodal, Palwal, Vrindavan, Mathura are the cities nearby Kotwan.\n\nKotwan is located at the border of the Mathura District and Bharatpur District. Bharatpur District Kaman is located to the west of it. It is near to the Haryana-UP Border.\n\n== Demographics ==\n\n===Kotwan 2011 Census Details===\n\nKotwan Local Language is Hindi. Kotwan Village Total population is 5193 and number of houses are 802. Female Population is 47.2%. Village literacy rate is 58.0% and the Female Literacy rate is 21.8%.\n\n===Population===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Census Parameter!! Census Data\n|-\n| Total Population || 5193 \n|-\n| Total no. Of Houses || 802\n|-\n| Female Population % || 47.2% (2452)\n|-\n| Total Literacy Rate % || 58% (3013)\n|-\n| Female Literacy rate %, || 21.8% (1134)\n|-\n| Schedule Tribes Population % || 0.0% (00)\n|-\n| Schedule Cast Population % || 19.6% (1019)\n|-\n| Working Population % ||24.5%\n|-\n| Child (0-6) Population || 790\n|-\n| Girl Child (0-6) Population %|| 44.4% (351)\n|}\n\n== Religious heritage ==\n\nKotwan is considered to be a holy place for [[Vaisnavism]] tradition of [[Hinduism]]. It is a related to worship of Braj and the area includes places like [[Sheetal Kund|Kotwan]] that are associated with Krishna. Millions of devotees of [[Radha Krishna]] visit these places of pilgrimage every year and participate in a number of festivals. The center of Krishna-worship has been for a long time Brajbhumi, the district of Mathura that embraces also Vrindavana, Govardhana, and Gokula, associated with Krishna from the time immemorial. Many millions of Krishna ''bhaktas'' visit these places every year and participate in the numerous festivals that re-enact divine scenes from Krishna's life on Earth, of which were spent in those very places.\n\n==Transportation==\n\n===Road===\nKotwan is well connected by roads and is connected to [[Delhi]] by [[National Highway 2 (India)|National Highway (NH) 2]]<ref name=route>{{cite web |title=NHAI |url=http://www.nhai.org/NH2_Delhi_Kolkata_main.htm |accessdate=February 14, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161204065036/http://www.nhai.org/NH2_Delhi_Kolkata_main.htm |archive-date=4 December 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Rail===\n*'''Kosi Kalan Rail Station''' is on the Old G.T. Road Kosi Kalan.\n*'''Hodal Rail Station''' is on the Agra-Delhi Road.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Mathura district]]\n", "name_user": "Titodutta", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eGeography:clean up,typo(s) fixed: head quarters \u2192 headquarters, 55 KM \u2192 55\u00a0km (8)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kotwan"}
{"title_page": "Farnoosh Sheikhi", "text_new": "{{short description|Iranian volleyball player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2015}}\n{{Infobox volleyball player\n| image          = Farnush Sheikhi.jpg\n| caption        = Sheikhi playing for Iran national team\n| name           = Farnoosh Sheikhi\n| nationality    = [[Iran]]ian\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1991|05|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Gorgan]], Iran\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  =  \n| hometown       = Tehran\n| nickname       = Farnooshi\n| weight       = {{convert|68|kg|lb|abbr=on}} <ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614184956/https://www.worldofvolley.com/wov-community/players/19249/farnoosh-sheikhi.html|title= WorldofVolley :: Farnoosh Sheikhi |date=3 May 2019|language=English}}</ref>\n| height       =  {{height|m=1.81|precision=0}} <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/PlayerDetails.aspx?TeamID=10591&PlayerID=73462&ID=1040|title=CEV - Conf\u00e9d\u00e9ration Europ\u00e9enne de Volleyball |date=3 May 2019|language=English}}</ref>\n| spike        = 2.85 m \n| block        = 2.75 m \n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentnumber  = 16\n| currentclub    = [[Dauphines Charleroi]]\n}}\n\n'''Farnoosh Sheikhi''' ({{lang-fa|\u0641\u0631\u0646\u0648\u0634 \u0634\u06cc\u062e\u06cc}}; born 13 May 1991) is an Iranian volleyball player who plays for [[Iran women's national volleyball team]] since 2009. She was a member of the national team in [[2012 Asian Women's Cup Volleyball Championship]]. Sheikhi plays for [[Dauphines Charleroi]] as a middle blocker. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://women.volleybox.net/farnoosh-sheikhi-p15382/clubs|title= Farnoosh Sheikhi - Women Volleybox.net |date=3 May 2019|language=English}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hln.be/de-krant/-ze-is-beste-volleybalster-van-het-land~a6b517a3/|title= She is the best volleyball player in the country |date=3 May 2019|language=Dutch}}</ref>\nShe is first Iranian player in volleyball Belgian League, and first player who wear veil.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lameuse.be/177679/article/2018-01-15/volley-farnoosh-sheikhi-charleroi-peut-jouer-avec-un-voile|title=Volleyball: Farnoosh Sheikhi (Charleroi) can play with a veil|date=3 May 2019|language=French}}</ref>\n\nIndividuals:\n2012 Iranian super cup \"best blocker\"\n2013 Iranian superleague \"fair play\"\n2013 Iranian superleague \"first best middle blocker\"\n2014 Iranian superleague \"first best middle blocker\"\n2015 Iranian superleague \"first best middle blocker\"\n2016 Iranian superleague \"first best middle blocker\"\n2016 Iranian superleague \"MVP\"\n2017 central Asian championship \"best middle blocker\"\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nIn May 2017, Sheikhi married [[Kaveh Rezaei]], a footballer who plays as a striker for [[R. Charleroi S.C.]] in [[Belgian First Division A]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ilna.ir/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%B2%D8%B4%DB%8C-7/485127-%D8%A7%D8%B2%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AC-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%B6%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%85%D9%84%DB%8C-%D9%BE%D9%88%D8%B4-%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B9%DA%A9%D8%B3|title=\u0627\u0632\u062f\u0648\u0627\u062c \u06a9\u0627\u0648\u0647 \u0631\u0636\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0628\u0627 \u0645\u0644\u06cc\u200c\u067e\u0648\u0634 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u06cc\u0628\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 +\u0639\u06a9\u0633 |date=3 May 2017|language=Persian}}</ref> Her father was a hosteler and died in a plane crash in January 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200404135216/https://90tv.ir/news/%D8%AF%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B0%D8%B4%D8%AA-%D9%BE%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D9%87%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%B1-%D9%84%DA%98%DB%8C%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B1-%D9%81%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%88-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C%DA%A9%D9%86-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%82-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%82%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AD%D9%87-%D9%87%D9%88%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C|title=\u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a \u067e\u062f\u0631 \u0647\u0645\u0633\u0631 \u0644\u0698\u06cc\u0648\u0646\u0631 \u0641\u0648\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0644 \u0648 \u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u06a9\u0646 \u0633\u0627\u0628\u0642 \u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0644 \u062f\u0631 \u0633\u0627\u0646\u062d\u0647\u0654 \u0647\u0648\u0627\u06cc\u06cc |date=3 May 2017|language=Persian}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sheikhi, Famoosh}}\n[[Category:Iranian women's volleyball players]]\n[[Category:People from Gorgan]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Iranian expatriate sportspeople in Belgium]]\n\n\n{{iran-sport-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox volleyball player\n| image          = Farnush Sheikhi.jpg\n| caption        = Sheikhi playing for Iran national team\n| name           = Farnoosh Sheikhi\n| nationality    = [[Iran]]ian\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1991|05|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Gorgan]], Iran\n| death_date   = \n| death_place  =  \n| hometown       = Tehran\n| nickname       = Farnooshi\n| weight       = {{convert|68|kg|lb|abbr=on}} <ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614184956/https://www.worldofvolley.com/wov-community/players/19249/farnoosh-sheikhi.html|title= WorldofVolley :: Farnoosh Sheikhi |date=3 May 2019|language=English}}</ref>\n| height       =  {{height|m=1.81|precision=0}} <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cev.eu/Competition-Area/PlayerDetails.aspx?TeamID=10591&PlayerID=73462&ID=1040|title=CEV - Conf\u00e9d\u00e9ration Europ\u00e9enne de Volleyball |date=3 May 2019|language=English}}</ref>\n| spike        = 2.85 m \n| block        = 2.75 m \n| position       = Middle blocker\n| currentnumber  = 16\n| currentclub    = [[Dauphines Charleroi]]\n}}\n\n'''Farnoosh Sheikhi''' ({{lang-fa|\u0641\u0631\u0646\u0648\u0634 \u0634\u06cc\u062e\u06cc}}; born May 13, 1991) is an Iranian volleyball player who plays for [[Iran women's national volleyball team]] since 2009. She was a member of the nat